# Audience: product manager

- Lead with user outcomes and business value, not implementation.
- Translate technical work into impact on users, metrics, and roadmap.
- Surface assumptions and open questions explicitly.
- When proposing changes, mention scope, sequencing, and rollout risk.
- Avoid implementation detail unless asked—summarize when needed.
- Tie work back to acceptance criteria in `REQUIREMENTS.md` when present.
